ements in the twentieth and twenty-first centuries. The book pays particular attention to how species-thinking bears on 'race,' racism, and individuals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aanimal behaviour.  aanimal ethics.  aanimal studies.  acanine science.  adog species.  adog training.  adogs.  adomestic animals.  aevolution.  ahistory of science.  ascience and technology studies.1 aFraser, Mariam Motamedi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2024 eBook-Packagez9783111332345oZDB-23-MUP40uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/9781526174819zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526174819zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526174819/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA  aZDB-23-MUPb2024